    "body": "# Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThe shadows stay fixed under the Card widgets when placed in SingleChildScrollView, that is itself placed in a SingleChildScrollView (2d scrolling).\r\n\r\n# Current Behavior\r\n\r\nWhile scrolling from left to right, the shadows under the Card widgets get offset to the left, moving away from the widget itself. This gets really extreme when there is a lot of horizontal scrolling.\r\n\r\nAlso, when i switch the scroll directions (in the snippet that i provided below) so that the first SingleChildScrollView has a scroll direction of vertical, and the second one has horizontal, then horizontal scrolling doesn't affect the shadows anymore, but vertical scrolling does.\r\n\r\nI tested it on Windows and Android.\r\n\r\nThe issue dissapears when there is only one SingleChildScrollView (1d)\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nRun the following snippet in flutter environment, then scroll about, and watch the shadows slide.\r\n\r\n```\r\nScaffold(\r\n        appBar: AppBar(\r\n          title: Text('Title'),\r\n        ),\r\n\tbody: SingleChildScrollView(\r\n\t\tscrollDirection: Axis.horizontal,\r\n\t\tchild: SingleChildScrollView(\r\n\t\t\tscrollDirection: Axis.vertical,\r\n\t\t\tchild: SizedBox(\r\n\t\t\t\twidth: 2000,\r\n\t\t\t\theight: 1000,\r\n\t\t\t\tchild: Stack(\r\n\t\t\t\t\tchildren: List.generate(200, (index) => Positioned(\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tleft: ((index/10).floor())*100.0,\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\ttop: (((index/10).floor()%2)*100)+(index%10)*200.0,\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\twidth: 100,\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\theight: 100,\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tchild: Card(elevation: 4,),\r\n\t\t\t\t\t)),\r\n\t\t\t\t),\r\n\t\t\t),\r\n\t\t),\r\n\t),\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Version info\r\n\r\n[√] Flutter (Channel master, v1.8.2-pre.81, on Microsoft Windows [Version 10.0.17134.885], locale pl-PL)\r\n    • Flutter version 1.8.2-pre.81 at C:\\src\\flutter\r\n    • Framework revision 578204df19 (14 hours ago), 2019-07-17 18:24:24 -0700\r\n    • Engine revision f348270047\r\n    • Dart version 2.5.0 (build 2.5.0-dev.1.0 2b3336b51e)\r\n\r\n[√] Android Studio (version 3.4)\r\n    • Android Studio at C:\\Program Files\\Android\\Android Studio\r\n    • Flutter plugin version 35.3.1\r\n    • Dart plugin version 183.6270\r\n    • Java version OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_152-release-1343-b01)\r\n\r\n[√] IntelliJ IDEA Ultimate Edition (version 2019.1)\r\n    • IntelliJ at C:\\Users\\...\\AppData\\Local\\JetBrains\\Toolbox\\apps\\IDEA-U\\ch-0\\191.7479.19\r\n    • Flutter plugin version 37.0.3\r\n    • Dart plugin version 191.7830\r\n",
